
                                            A 36-year-old man has been arrested in Muizenberg for the possession of three unlicensed firearms.
                                         CAPE TOWN - A 36-year-old man has been arrested in Muizenberg for the possession of three unlicensed firearms. Police say the public alerted authorities to the suspicious vehicle. It was further discovered that the vehicle the suspect was travelling in was stolen. The police’s Andre Traut said: “The driver, a 36-year-old man, was arrested and the vehicle searched, which led to the discovery of three unlicensed firearms. Once charged, the suspect will make a court appearance in Muizenberg.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)